Class Handlers

  • java.lang.Object
    • k23b.am.rest.Handlers

  • @Path(value="handle/")
public class Handlers
extends java.lang.Object
    A class for the handling of the REST communication between the AM and SA using methods that listen to certain URIs.

                                                                                                                                                                                        java.lang.String hashKey,
                                                                                                                                                                                        @PathParam(value="nmapVersion")
                                                                                                                                                                                        java.lang.String nmapVersion,

                                                                                                                                                                                        java.lang.String osVersion,

                                                                                                                                                                                        @PathParam(value="deviceName")
                                                                                                                                                                                        java.lang.String deviceName)
        The AM gets a request from the SA with the following parameters.
        Parameters:
        hashKey - The hashkey of the SA who makes the request.
        nmapVersion - The version of nmap that the SA who makes the request has.
        osVersion - The version of OS that the SA who makes the request has.
        interfaceMAC - The MAC address that the SA who makes the request has.
        interfaceIP - The IP address that the SA who makes the request has.
        deviceName - The device name that the SA who makes the request has.
        Returns:
        A Response to the SA with either a code error status or a code success and the request status.
